Privacy Policy for SolarAid

Effective Date: 01/06/2023

SolarAid ("we," "us," or "our") is committed to protecting the privacy of our users. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, store, and share information collected through our mobile application, SolarAid.

Information We Collect:

Solar Array Data: SolarAid collects data about solar arrays and their locations. This information is stored locally on the user's device and may be sent to third-party services such as forecast.solar to provide production forecasts.

Analytical Data: We automatically collect analytical data on app usage, such as session duration and features accessed. This data is collected using Google Analytics.

How We Use Collected Information:

Functionality: Solar array data is used to provide production forecasts to users. Analytical data is used to improve the functionality and user experience of the app.
Data Storage and Protection:

Solar Array Data: Solar array data is stored locally on the user's device and is transmitted securely to third-party services for forecasting purposes.

Analytical Data: Analytical data is stored securely by Google Analytics.

Sharing of Information:

Third-Party Services: Solar array data may be shared with third-party services such as forecast.solar to provide production forecasts.
User Privacy Options:

Data Deletion: Users can request the deletion of their data by contacting us at solaraid-privacy@brown1993.com.
Contact Us:

If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy or data practices, you can contact us at solaraid-privacy@brown1993.com.

No Other Privacy Considerations:

There are no other relevant privacy considerations specific to SolarAid.

Changes to This Privacy Policy:

We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting the updated Privacy Policy on the app.
